JORKLE SPUNK RULES (Est: 04/13/2026)

Before the game starts the group determines what phases they want to play, and the order they want to play them in.

Next each player is randomly assigend a secret task. The Goal is to complete your secret task without giving it away. The player who wins activate the "Secret Phase", and gets a reward for that phase. See Secret Phase for details.

The Goal of the game is to finish with the most points. Points are awarder throughout the phases.

By winning a phase you are awarded a ZORK. ZORKs can be spent is DA SCHLOP for rewards!

A player is disqualified if they vomit, forfit, or deny a drink,

JORKLE: Allows a player to gift a drink of their choosing to an opposing player. This may be used at anytime during the game. A JORKLE may consist of ONLY 3 units of alcohol. (Ex. 2 shots and 1 beer). The player must also take a sip of the JORKLE before gifting it to insure it is not poisoned.

If a player comits a Party Foul they are punished by taking 1 drink.

Party Fouls:
 - Spillage
 - Falling Over
 - Breaking Something
 - Farting
 - Breaking an Egg
 - Violence

The Game offically start by listening to the song "Arthur" by Rick Wakeman in complete silence. At the end of the song take a shot and begin the first phase!

If a player speaks while the opening song(or JORKLE SPUNK Symphony) is playing, they must take 1 drink!